<div class="ui container">
  <div class="ui segment header-text">
    <p>Three weeks after the death of George Floyd at the hands of Minneapolis police and the tumultuous protests that followed, RPS school board met on June 15th to receive an overview of the memorandum of understanding (MOU) with the Richmond Police Department.</p>
    <p>On that same night, the school board received 47 pages of public comment, with many city residents urging the board and the administration to terminate the MOU. At that meeting, RPS administration recommended a 90-day in-depth review of the school resource officer program, during which time they would gather more data, hold focus groups with students and staff from all schools that have SROs, schedule a public hearing specifically on this issue, and research potential alternatives.</p>
    <p>We believe that all Richmond residents should have a voice in this issue and urge the school board to terminate the MOU. Please use the form below to tell your school board member that what our schools need are counselors and mental health providers, not police in our schools.</p>
  </div>
